      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KARBINE (4) is in terrific form having won his last two outings at this circuit and distance, one of them from a wider barrier than this. Going well enough to take this next step up in grade and land the hat trick. CENTURION DREAM (5) led and stuck on on to place here two back then gave her opponents no chance last start when she cruised to a 10.6 metre victory at Terang. Finds a tougher race but another win is not out of the question. CARLA PIXIE NZ (7) makes her first appearance since tackling the Breeders Crown 3F Final in December. Draws wide but two recent trial wins suggest she is back in good order. THE SKY IS THE LIMIT (2) is aided by a good draw and came from the back line to get within a neck of KARBINE as runner-up at this circuit and distance last time out.",
